    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know Pinjarra Hills well. I understand what motivates a prestige acreage buyer, how to position a property to attract national interest, and how to manage the longer campaign cycles this market demands. Selling well in Pinjarra Hills is not the same job as selling well in an inner-city suburb, and that distinction matters.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The suburb is bordered by Moggill Conservation Park and the Brisbane River, and access via Pinjarra Road and Sugars Road connects through to Kenmore and the Western Freeway. Equestrian holdings, vineyards in private hands and architect-designed residences on cleared elevated land are the highest-performing assets here. Properties with quality infrastructure such as machinery sheds, sealed driveways, dam water access and arena-ready paddocks consistently outperform raw acreage at sale.
    </p>
